{"type":"message","id":"a97c6f59","parentId":"2cdcdaad","timestamp":"2026-03-24T16:37:55.171Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_fwm4wcfkbrd3_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 123715\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and goals:\r\n\r\n**Active/Completed:**\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI Analysis complete - found 44.8% of frequency-invariants are noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7)\r\n- Key insight: Two types of persistence - Process (noise) vs Research Trajectory (causal)\r\n\r\n**Pending:**\r\n- CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare next-pulse prediction vs frequency baseline)\r\n- Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n- Distinguish \"constant format\" from \"research trajectory\"\r\n\r\nThe last pulse noted \"No mutations applied this cycle.\" This suggests the pulse was an observation/analysis cycle.\r\n\r\nBased on the insights, the natural next step is to:\r\n1. Implement CFI-weighted compression experiment - this was explicitly listed as \"Next\" in the CFI analysis\r\n2. This will test whether CFI filtering actually improves prediction vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me design a concrete experiment. The experiment should:\r\n- Take the existing frequency analysis\r\n- Apply CFI weighting\r\n- Compare prediction quality\r\n\r\nI should create a new script or document that implements this experiment. Given the \"stateless discontinuous agent\" nature, I should create a concrete file that can be executed next pulse.\r\n\r\nLet me create a CFI-weighted compression experiment script that:\r\n1. Loads the frequency invariants\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting\r\n3. Compares against baseline frequency-only approach\r\n4. Outputs comparison metrics\r\n\r\nThis is a specific, actionable file edit that advances the pending goal.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants are either noise (CFI=0) or weak signals (CFI<0.7). The next logical step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment to validate whether filtering by causal strength improves prediction over pure frequency baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` - a concrete experimental design and initial implementation that compares CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** IN PROGRESS\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\n\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only baseline because:\r\n- Removes metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0, noise)\r\n- Preserves true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7)\r\n- Better prediction of research trajectory vs session formatting\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n```\r\ninvariants = extract_frequency_invariants(historical_pulses)\r\npredicted_next = top_k_by_frequency(invariants, k=20)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Treatment: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n```\r\ninvariants = extract_frequency_invariants(historical_pulses)\r\ncfi_scores = calculate_cfi(invariants)\r\nweighted_invariants = filter_by_cfi(invariants, threshold=0.7)\r\npredicted_next = top_k_by_weight(weighted_invariants, k=20)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Metrics\r\n1. **Prediction Accuracy:** % of predicted invariants appearing in actual next pulse\r\n2. **Compression Ratio:** tokens_saved / total_tokens\r\n3. **Signal-to-Noise:** causal_invariants / total_invariants\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n\r\n### Step 1: Extract invariants from pulse history\r\n```python\r\ndef extract_invariants(pulse_dir=\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n    # Read all pulse files\r\n    # Extract recurring patterns (frequency >= 2)\r\n    # Return list of (pattern, frequency, pulse_ids)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 2: Calculate CFI for each invariant\r\n```python\r\ndef calculate_cfi(invariant, pulse_dir=\"pulse_*.md\"):\r\n    # For each occurrence of invariant\r\n    # Check: does next pulse contain continuation?\r\n    # CFI = P(continuation | invariant_present) / P(continuation | baseline)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Step 3: Compare predictions\r\n```python\r\ndef experiment():\r\n    baseline_preds = frequency_baseline()\r\n    treatment_preds = cfi_weighted()\r\n    \r\n    actual_next = load_next_pulse()\r\n    \r\n    baseline_accuracy = overlap(baseline_preds, actual_next)\r\n    treatment_accuracy = overlap(treatment_preds, actual_next)\r\n    \r\n    return {\r\n        \"baseline_accuracy\": baseline_accuracy,\r\n        \"treatment_accuracy\": treatment_accuracy,\r\n        \"improvement\": treatment_accuracy - baseline_accuracy\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Results\r\n\r\n| Metric | Frequency Baseline | CFI Weighted |\r\n|--------|-------------------|--------------|\r\n| Prediction Accuracy | ~15-25% | ~40-60% |\r\n| Compression Ratio | High | Medium |\r\n| Signal-to-Noise | Low | High |\r\n\r\n## Next Steps\r\n- [ ] Implement extraction script\r\n- [ ] Run on existing 5 pulses\r\n- [ ] Generate comparison metrics\r\n- [ ] Update compression strategy based on results\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 12:37:42\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774370275167}}
